Name: Glen Eagle Golf Club - Blue + Yellow
Oakmont CC
Description: Home to the 2016 US Open this course needs no introduction.  With its numerous bunkers and punishing greens it will test the skill of even the most elite golfers.

Name: Pasatiempo
Description:
Pasatiempo was designed by world-renowned golf architect Alister MacKenzie. Even though MacKenzie also designed Augusta National and Cypress Point, Pasatiempo was his favorite layout and where he made his American home.
COURSE DESCRIPTION
Can a golf course exist in harmony with its natural surroundings? At Pasatiempo, we believe that a golf course that acts responsibly can actually improve the environment. By providing green, open spaces in a residential area for wildlife and making extra efforts to preserve the habitat for wildlife. By providing a place for golfers of all ages to walk and enjoy nature â€” Pasatiempo is a fabulous course to walk, and the majority of golfers at Pasatiempo walk the course, taking advantage of our temperate climate and gently rolling terrain. And by maintaining the course with an awareness that we arenâ€™t simply running a golf course, weâ€™re a steward for the land that we work and play on here every day.

Name: Lake Caroline GC
Description:
Lake Caroline Golf Club is a private, 18 hole championship golf course located inside the premier lake community in Madison County. Designed around the scenic 850-acre Lake Caroline, this beautiful links course stretches to 6,800 yards, demanding accurate ball-striking and a little course management. 

pakmangolfstudios@gmail.com

Name: The Shoals Golf Club - Fighting Joe
Souris Valley GC
Description:
Souris Valley is just a short distance from the Lewis and Clark Trail.  This 18-hole course measures 6,759 yards from the tips and plays to a par-72. The Souris River winds through the course, and you will cross it about half a dozen times during your round. Four tee boxes give players of any ability a chance to test their golfing skills and have an enjoyable round of golf.

pakmangolfstudios@gmail.com

Name: Lely Resort - Mustang Club
Description: Welcome to Lely Resort Golf & Country Club. Located in southwest Florida's (Naples) beautiful Gulf Coast, Lely Resort Golf & Country Club is home to 54 holes of spectacular golf designed by three of golf’s most legendary names. The Mustang course is a Top 50 Resort Course by Golf World Magazine. Designed by Lee Trevino, The Mustang adheres to his philosophy that the game should be challenging, yet a fair challenge, for the common golfer. While many of The Mustang’s holes are demanding, they also offer players the opportunity to recover from errant shots. The course opened in 1996, and has since provided thousands of golfers with an extraordinary golfing experience.

Name: Glacier Gulph Club
Description: Formed in the demented mind of course designer Masta_Blasta, Glacier Gulph Club is based on the real life course 'Rock Creek' in Nicholson, PA. Masta_Blasta took Rock Creek and exaggerated its unique qualities to form a 'hybrid' course which could exist in real life if Rock Creek was built on an unlimited budget and wild imagination.  In real life, Rock Creek is a bit short at 4800 yards, but Glacier Gulph Club (GGC) merges several of the short par 3 holes into par 4s.  Masta_Blasta also added twonew par 5s. Hole 18 is a monster 650 yard downhill play. The 10th is a 550 yards split fairway with an island green. Enjoy the 5 waterfalls, great views, and most importantly hit 'em straight!

Name: Northport Golf Club
Description: Northport Golf Club in Northport, Maine

Name: Bucks Run Golf Club
Description: Jerry Matthews designed course hosts 18 challenging, yet playable holes, artfully sculpted fairways and tee boxes, soft sand bunkers, and more. The course also features river frontage, picturesque lakes, and natural wetlands coming into play on numerous holes.

Name: Vardon Golf Club
Description: Vardon Golf Club, located in Minot ND, is one of the finest golf courses open to public play in the upper Midwest. The quick greens are defended by well-placed bunkers requiring accurate approach shots.

Name: Lely Resort - Flamingo Island
Description: Welcome to Lely Resort Golf & Country Club. Located in southwest Florida's (Naples) beautiful Gulf Coast, Lely Resort Golf & Country Club is home to 54 holes of spectacular golf designed by three of golf’s most legendary names. The Flamingo Course opened for play in 1991. Robert Trent Jones, Sr. considers the Flamingo Course to be the finest public course he has ever designed. It's located on rigorous terrain with a large variety of hazards. Five sets of tee boxes make this course interesting for all skill levels. The fairways are tree lined, and the greens are fast and undulating. The signature hole is #5, a 200-yard, par 3, requiring a tee shot to an island green. Lakes come into play on eleven holes.

Name: Trump National Golf Club Philadelphia
Description: Trump National Philadelphia is an exclusive golf club conveniently located near Center City. Members enjoy panoramic views of Philadelphia from the award-winning Tom Fazio Course and a state-of-the-art practice facility.

Name: Castle Pines Golf Club
Description: Castle Pines Golf Club is the top-ranked course in Colorado, recognized for hosting The INTERNATIONAL tournament, a PGA Tour stop for 21 years (until the players complained too much about walking the elevation changes). The Castle Pines Golf Club is fashioned after Augusta National in Georgia. Membership is an invitation-only.  The course plays 7600 yards from the tips and features numerous elevation changes and water hazards.   Castle Pines has been chosen as the site for the 2024 BMW Championship.

Name: Bent Creek GC
Description:
Since Bent Creek's opening in 1989, the 6,620-yard, Par 71 course has provided a fun and challenging golf experience for residents of Northeast Florida and visitors alike.

Crafted by renowned architect Bobby Weed with consulting services by Mark McCumber, Bent Creek's meandering terrain takes golfers through a certified Audubon Cooperative Sanctuary, towering pines, and alongside creeks and swales. The championship layout boasts Bermuda grass greens, plush fairways and a state-of-the-art lighted practice facility which is home to the Bent Creek Golf Academy.

Name: St Georges Golf and Country Club
Description: Stanley Thompson’s masterfully designed course has truly stood the test of time. Ranked among the world’s finest courses, St. George’s offers a premier golf and country club escape from life’s hustle and bustle, nestled among the tree-lined streets of Toronto Ontario. The Club has received much praise from noted tour players for its traditional design, most notably its four outstanding finishing holes.

Name: The Grove XXIII
Description: Jordan’s course is named The Grove XXIII, with the Roman numeral 23 a nod, obviously, to Jordan’s number with the Chicago Bulls. The club, located in Hobe Sound, Florida, officially opened in the fall of 2019.

Name: Furry Creek Golf and CC
Description:
Please allow a few minutes for initial load.

Regarded as one of the most scenic courses in North America, this unique mountain course has 6 par 3's 6par 4's and 6 par 5's.  

Relatively short from the tips at a touch over 6000 yards you will still find this course very challenging.

You may recognize this course from Happy Gilmore as it was used for the Pepsi Pro Am, and the iconic fist fight between Happy and Bob Barker happened right on the 9th green.

Name: Pine Needles GC
Description: Just minutes from both historic downtown Southern Pines and the Village of Pinehurst, Pine Needles Lodge & Golf Club is the perfect golf retreat. Known for its superior golf instruction, cozy ambiance and immaculate Donald Ross course, Pine Needles lives up to its reputation as a sanctuary of excellence.

Name: Abacoa Golf Club
Description: The Abacoa Golf Course was the last course designed by renowned course architect Joe Lee before his death. In typical Joe Lee style, Abacoa’s lakes and bunkers meet its sloping fairways with little obstruction, and you’ll find scenic views with 14 of its 18 holes surrounded by water. All of these features make the tees, greens, and fairways a pure pleasure to play.

Name: Cheyenne Shadows
Description: Sitting on the Fort Carson Army Base in Colorado Spring, CO.  Cheyenne Shadows Golf Course is an 18 hole, championship golf course situated at the base of Cheyenne Mountain.

Name: Pitt Meadows
Description: Since 1963, the Pitt Meadows Golf Club has offered its members, guests and the public a delightful golf experience combined with unmatched camaraderie. It provides a championship calibre challenge but an enjoyable and walkable experience. From perfectly manicured lawns to the picturesque backdrop of the Golden Ears Mountains, the setting is as nice as they come.

Name: Arizona National Golf Club
Description: Arizona National Golf Club, designed by Robert Trent Jones Jr, was voted best public golf course in Tucson, Arizona. Nestled in the foothills of the beautiful Santa Catalina Mountains and abutting the Coronado National Forest, Arizona National follows the rugged natural flow of the land across shady mesquite-lined arroyos and skirts craggy rock outcroppings.

Name: Lely Resort - The Classics
Description: Welcome to Lely Resort Golf & Country Club. Located in southwest Florida's (Naples) beautiful Gulf Coast, Lely Resort Golf & Country Club is home to 54 holes of spectacular golf designed by three of golf’s most legendary names. The exlusive private Classics course was designed by Gary Player and has hosted the Champions Tour Chubb Classic. The resort is also home to the publicly accessible Flamingo Island and Mustang courses designed by Robert Trent Jones, Sr. and Lee Trevino, respectively. Abundant water and swaying palm trees frame undulating fairways and pristine greens, creating a serene and stunning atmosphere for relaxation, rejuvenation, and a great game of golf.

Name: Bayside Golf Club
Description:
Bayside Golf Club is a family built and family owned public golf course and along with world-famous architects Dan Axland and Dave Proctor who had a hand in designing such legends as Sand Hills Golf Club in Mullen, NE and the rebuild of famed Riviera Country Club in Los Angeles, CA.

The average length from the middle tees is 6,148 yards and plays to a par 72. This public course is a link style course featuring wide open fairways, and 4 characteristic par 3’s that range from canyon carries to bunkers in the green.

Name: Big Fish Golf Club
Description:
“Big fish” tales are a concept that golfers are almost as familiar with as the fishermen themselves. The “Big Fish” in this club’s title is a literal reference to angling, however, as the National Freshwater Hall of Fame is just down the road in Hayward, Wisconsin. The proprietors were able to hook a big one when they landed an architect for the property: Pete Dye. The Kohler resort on Lake Michigan (including Whistling Straits and Blackwood Run) is perhaps the most celebrated location in Dye’s oeuvre, however he got away to a more isolated location in the state for this development. 
This course is a story of two nines, with the front being laid out among grassland, while the back winds its way through a forest. Those trees rarely come into play however, with most agreeing the windy first-half of the round will play considerably more difficult. 
Somewhat ironically — both for a designer noted for his water hazards, and for a town noted for its fishing history — there is only one hole at Big Fish where you could potentially catch a big fish.

Name: Royal Liverpool (members layout)
Description: Royal Liverpool, also known as ‘Hoylake’ is over 150 years old and has hosted The Open 12 times. The last 2 winners being Tiger Woods in 2006 and Rory McIlroy in 2014. Players should be wary of the internal out of bounds that protects the practice area, and the brutal pot bunkers. The Open returns there in 2023.

Name: Country Club of Jackson
Description: Redesigned in 2008/09 by John Fought, Dogwood-Azalea comprises CC of Jackson's championship 18. The course offers five tee locations and plays anywhere from 7,400 - 5,100 yards.  It annually hosts the Sanderson Farms Championship on the PGA Tour.

Name: Avon Fields Golf Course
Description: Avon Fields Golf Course is Cincinnati's historic classic golf course, set on a beautiful rolling terrain of tree-lined fairways, just minutes from downtown. Challenging and fun for players of all abilities, the course's small, elevated greens perfect a player's short game skills.

Name: Fossil Trace Golf Club
Description:
The link between a prehistoric past and the modern golf course is here for you to discover.

Fossil Trace Golf Club opened July 2003 in the historic city of Golden, Colorado, nestled adjacent to the foothills of the Rocky Mountain Front Range, just 20 minutes west from downtown Denver. Fossil Trace is considered one of Denver’s top golf courses and premier destinations to play. Golfers can experience a mountain course feel in an urban setting.

In addition to the prehistoric relics at Fossil Trace Golf Club, several massive remnants of clay mining equipment can be seen throughout the golf course layout. Each piece serves as a reminder of the rich history of the property and adds to the award-winning golf experience.  head up to 5700 ft and enjoy some Colorado Foothills Golf!

Name: Mountain Top Golf Course
Description: This short, 13-hole course lacks nothing short of a remarkable experience for golfers. Intertwined through unforgettable rock formations, Mountain Top Course includes some of the most dramatic views in the Ozarks. With thousands of hours put into pick and shovel excavations, 300-million year old limestone formations were revealed, adding to the unparalleled, over-the-top experience that is Mountain Top Course.

Name: Pelton Sands
Description: Pelton Sands is a fictional golf course.

Name: Heritage Shores
Description: Heritage Shores is an Arthur Hills designed classic links style championship golf course located in Bridgeville, Delaware. With an array of strategically incorporated bunkers and undulating fairways, coupled with the water obstacles, this par 72 golf course will challenge and test each player’s abilities.

Name: Forsyth Country Club
Description: Established in 1913, this Donald Ross designed golf course has been highly touted and one of the best in North Carolina. Similar to Pinehurst many greens are crowned so approaches need to be accurate and have staying power. The front nine has elevated tees and greens and a few blind shots mixed in. The back nine is more open and forgiving but still challenging. As opposed to most courses the Red Tees are the Tips at 6600 yards

Name: Minot AFB Rough Rider GC
Description: The Rough Rider Golf Course is a challenging nine-hole course located near Minot Air Force Base and can be entered directly from US Highway 83. Golfers don’t have to go through the base gate, and the course is open to the public. The course is essential to the entertainment and recreation program at Minot Air Force Base, and is managed and maintained in a relaxed, friendly atmosphere including a driving range, putting green, chipping green, and picnic area.

Name: Mohall CC
Description: Mohall CC

Name: Randolph North Golf Course
Description: Randolph opened in 1925, and was the site of the P.G.A. Seiko Tucson Match Play Championship, the P.G.A. Joe Garagiola Tucson Open and the PING/Welch's LPGA Championship. It is Tucson City Golf's longest golf course, measuring 6,900 yards from the championship tees and just short of 6,000 from the front tees. The course setting is a scenic one with numerous tall trees, lush fairways, and a beautiful view of the mountains surrounding Tucson. The course features water hazards on five holes and long fairways. Randolph shares the Randolph Golf Complex with the Dell Urich Golf Course.

Name: Randolph Dell Urich
Description: The centrally located, Dell Urich opened in 1996 after complete re-design on the site of the former Randolph South Golf Course. The dramatic makeover features spectacular views from four sets of tees, and dramatic elevation changes. Dell Urich is the former home of the Tucson LPGA tour stop. It measures more than 6,600 yards from the back tees, and almost 5,300 from the fronts. Golfers can enjoy a great round of golf, and beautiful scenery at Dell Urich. This course shares the Randolph Golf Complex with the Randolph North Golf Course.

Name: Whitinsville Golf Club
Description: Whitinsville Golf Club in Whitinsville Massachusetts.

Name: Rich Harvest Farms
Description: When it officially opened in 1999, Rich Harvest Farms was rated the 5th Best New Private Golf Course by Golf Digest. Three years later, Golf Digest placed the course on “America’s 100 Greatest Golf Courses,” where it remains to this day.   Since its opening, Rich Harvest Farms has become a premiere destination for golfers from all over the world, attracting a series of prestigious amateur and professional tournaments, including the 2009 Solheim Cup and 2022 LIV Golf Tour Chicago.

Name: Broadmoor West
Description: Get ready for rolling fairways, multi-level greens, and demanding hazards at the stunning yet formidable West Course. At 6,800 feet, this 18-hole course has more doglegs and steeply-angled greens than the East Course, and offers breathtaking views of both the mountains and Colorado Springs. The West Course plays tighter off the tee, with more heavily tree-lined holes than the East Course, and also gives players an array of spectacular approach shots. Don't let the stunning mountain views distract you; our West Course may look like a postcard, but it offers a very challenging and rewarding round of golf. The West Course was also the host site of the 1998 PGA Cup Matches.

Name: Shadow Creek Golf Club
Description: Known as the home of THE MATCH between Tiger and Phil.  The course is carved in the middle of the Vegas desert and presents a challenge to all golfers.

Name: Berry Hill Golf Course
Description: Bridgeton Berry Hill is a great 9 hole regulation course located at the Berry Hill Golf Course facility in Bridgeton, MO. From the longest tees it offers 2,922 yards of golf for a par of 36. The course was designed by and opened in 1967.

Name: Silverado Resort & Spa - North
Description: Challenge yourself on a championship course, surrounded by Napa Valley’s golden hills. Redesigned by PGA Hall-of-Famer Johnny Miller, the North course is the permanent home of PGA's Fortinet Championship.

Name: The Hay
Description:
The Hay has been a fixture at Pebble Beach since 1957, when famed Head Professional Peter Hay revolutionized the concept of a short course. Hay’s vision was to create a fun place where juniors, families, and friends, regardless of their ability, could gather around the game of golf.

In 2021, Tiger Woods amplified Hay’s vision in a way few could have imagined with his brilliant redesign of the property. The result is a course overflowing with fun, including an exact replica of the famed No. 7 at Pebble Beach Golf Links, as well as holes designed to be played with any club in the bag, and an additional 20,000 square-foot putting course that sprawls 100 yards, yielding endless routings.

It’s Pebble Beach, the Tiger Woods way. Play The Hay!

Name: The Australian Golf Club
Description: Hosting a record 21 Australian Opens, The Australian Golf Club in Sydney, Australia is one of the most revered golf clubs in the country. Set just 6km from the CBD, this Alister McKenzie/Jack Nicklaus masterpiece has tested the world's best with its tight fairways, small greens and strategically placed water hazards.

Name: Whistler Nicklaus North
Description: The Jack Nicklaus Signature Design par 71, 18-hole course winds along a gentle valley floor with towering mountains in the back drop.  Snowcapped mountain peaks, emerald lakes and majestic trees coupled with fresh mountain air provide a stellar backdrop at this award-winning golf course. Just minutes from the resort village of Whistler, British Columbia, Nicklaus North stands out as one of the great courses in North America. With a yardage of 6,925 from the championship Nicklaus tees, the par 71 course will present an enjoyable challenge for even the most experienced golfers.  Enjoy Nicklaus North.

Name: Gates Four Golf and Country Club
Eldon Golf Club
Description: Eldon Golf Club offers an 18 hole championship course taking full advantage of the natural terrain. Located in Central Missouri at the edge of the beautiful Lake of the Ozarks, Eldon Golf Club resides amidst the original Sanning Homestead. Eldon Golf Club has recently been voted Best Overall Public Golf Club in Lake of the Ozarks as well as a 2009 Reader's Favorite.

Name: New South Wales Golf Club
Description:
This 1921 Alister MacKenzie masterpiece is the crown jewel of the Sydney, Australia golf scene. 

Hugging the cliff line of the Pacific Ocean, New South Wales Golf Club (NSW) is ranked the 47th best course in the world by Golf Magazine, yet is only 20 mins from the Sydney CBD. 

The two most famous holes are the par-5 5th, with its long, downward sloping fairway toward the Pacific, and the 195-yard 6th that plays over an inlet of Cape Banks, but the stretch from 13 to 16 is as good a run of par-4s as you will find anywhere. Wind can be your friend or foe throughout the journey, usually dictating golfers’ fortunes. New South Wales on a calm day is entirely playable but MacKenzie’s layout can turn into a beast. 

Be especially mindful of the waste areas on holes towards the shoreline. Most balls that entire these areas will be unplayable, making accuracy off the tee paramount.

Name: Tower Ranch
Description: Tower Ranch golf club was named the fourth best new golf course in the world by Travel and Leisure magazine and Golf Digest's top 3 in Canada. The links style design is carved out of BC's Kelowna hillside with panoramic views of the Okanagan mountains.  Tower Ranch offers tremendous elevation changes, 112 bunkers of which many are steep faced - that you will be spending time in - and tough greens that will challenge even the most seasoned putters. The course provides numerous risk/reward shotmaking opportunities that plays well for any level of golfer.  Enjoy Tower Ranch

Name: Coldwater Golf Links
Description: Coldwater Golf Links is an 18-hole public golf course located in Ames, Iowa. It is classic links-style course that was rated as a Golf Digest 4-Star Best Places to Play. The course is located next to Iowa State University and views Jack Trice Stadium.

Name: Hershey Parkview
Description: Hershey Parkview was commissioned by the founder of Hershey Chocolate, Milton Hershey, and designed by Maurice McCarthy. Hershey Park Golf Course (later named Parkview) was designed to serve as Hershey’s public course and bring golf to the 'common working man'. A challenging course, incorporating Spring Creek and its surrounding hills, the Park Golf Course, was reasonably priced and popular with community residents and visitors alike. For $1.00 ($1.50 on weekends) a player was entitled to play all day. Greens fees also included swimming privileges in the Hershey Park Pool. It was built in 1909 and was closed in 2004 to expand Hershey Park and the surrounding Giant Center Arena and Hershey Park Stadium

Name: Ames Golf and Country Club
Description: Ames Golf & Country Club is in Ames, Iowa. It was founded in 1911 as a 9-hole golf course and then relocated in 1971 to the current 18-hole layout. It is a park-style course with tree-lined fairways and some water-protected greens. It hosts several local high-school and college golf tournaments. Surrounded by flat corn fields, the central Iowa wind often challenges low scores.

Name: Veenker Memorial Golf Course
Description:
Veenker Memorial Golf Course  is a premier public golf facility owned and operated by Iowa State University in Ames, Iowa. The course opened for play in 1938 and was the vision of George F. Veenker, former ISU athletic director and football coach. A Perry Maxwell design, Veenker has since become one of the most talked about, demanding, challenging and fun-to-play golf courses in the Midwest. 

It is host to the Iowa Masters, an invitational golf tournament that is one of the Iowa Golf Association's major tournaments. The tournament has historically been the standard by which other tournaments around the state pattern themselves. The committee that runs the Iowa Masters dedicates themselves to preserving the history of the tournament while continuing to improve it for the benefit of amateur golfers.

The Iowa Masters is also a World Amateur golf rankings event.

Name: Wentworth West Course
Description:
Wentworth’s West course was originally designed by the legendary golf course architect Harry Colt and opened in 1926. Alterations by Ernie Els were made in the 2000s.

The course has played host to some of the world's most prestigious trophies; including The Ryder Cup, The World Match Play and the European Tour’s flagship event, the BMW PGA Championships.

Name: The Golf Club at Devils Tower
Shaughnessy Golf & Country Club
Description: A Vancouver landmark that’s rich in history and time-honoured traditions, Shaughnessy has welcomed world leaders, hosted historic matches between golf legends, and held numerous golf championships—including four Canadian Opens between 1948 and 2011.

Name: North Hants
Description:
The Golf course was originally designed by James Braid, and opened in 1904. Extensively redesigned in 1913 by Harry Colt and further improved in 1930 by Tom Simpson. More recently, three new holes were designed by Donald Steel in 2001. 

Each year the club hosts the “Hampshire Hog”. A 36 hole scratch competition for amateur golfers. Famous winners include Justin Rose, Sandy Lyle and Gordon Brand Jr.

Name: The Golf Club of New England
River Highlands CC
Description: River Highlands’ award-winning golf course boasts a tough finishing stretch from holes 15-18. The 15, 16 and 17th holes all play around a four-acre lake. Stewart Cink, who won the 2008 Travelers Championship, called them, “four of the most exciting finishing holes in a group anywhere in the world.”

Name: Garland Swampfire Course
Description:
A true assessment of your shot-making ability, with water hazards on all but two of the holes. 

Home of the signature number five horseshoe-shaped tee complex.

Generous fairways offer a blend of both left and right doglegs and green complexes.

Name: Kartano Golf
Description: Kartanogolf is a full-scale 18-hole golf course in Joroinen.  The field designed by Ake Person contains two nines that differ from each other. The park-like front is built on a fairly flat and open area, while the back, which is mainly built in the middle of the forest, also contains interesting differences in height. There are enough challenges for players of many levels!

Name: Carl's Place HQ Hole-in-One Challenge
Description: Test your skills with the Carl's Place HQ Hole-in-One Challenge. This custom course (or shot?) challenges you with a single shot over (and off of) the home of Carl, inspired by some famous professional golfer's social media stunts. Hit the green—or the roof—and see if you’ve got what it takes.

Name: White Horse Golf Club
Description: White Horse Golf Club is nestled among old growth fir, pine, and cedar trees and is considered one of Kitsap Peninsula’s finest golf locations, while also being one of the toughest courses in the Northwest.

Name: Garland Fountains Course
Description:
Challenging approach shots and undulating green complexes require strategy and accurate shots.

A unique 6-6-6 design, with several par 5’s.

Home of the famous log-style bridge and the original clubhouse.

Name: Garland Reflections Course
Description:
Slightly shorter than Garland’s other courses, with fewer forced carries, but shot placement is critical.

Lush fairways meander through majestic pines and northern Michigan hardwoods.

Feature 6 each par 3’s, 4’s, and 5’s. Several of the Par 3 holes are iconic.

Greens complexes are well bunkered with subtle green undulations.

Name: Garland Monarch Course
Description:
Garland’s longest course – a true championship test of golf.

Monarch is home to Garland’s resident bald eagles!

Very large green complexes and wide fairways allow you to ‘grip it and rip it’. 

Features well-bunkered greens and a favorable mix of left and right doglegs.

Name: Ledgeview Golf Course
Description: Combining playability with natural beauty, our classic course layout features rolling fairways, well bunkered greens, acres of picturesque wild flowers and gardens. For a relaxing, yet challenging round of golf that will bring you back again and again, make it Ledgeview Golf Course.

Name: Whisper Rock (Upper Course)
Description: Whisper Rock is a 36-hole private club. Membership is limited to less than 600 members, several of which are PGA players. The Upper Course was designed by Tom Fazio and opened in 2005. It sits on the north side of the property and is highlighted by the numerous rock outcroppings and dramatic mountain vistas.
